51
00:05:16,710 --> 00:05:20,470
He probably arrived safely, right?

52
00:05:20,470 --> 00:05:22,770
I hope so.

53
00:05:22,770 --> 00:05:26,630
Doesn't the hospital feel empty and gloomy without him?

54
00:05:26,630 --> 00:05:28,070
I'm here. Why would it feel gloomy?

55
00:05:28,070 --> 00:05:29,690
Oh, okay.

56
00:05:29,690 --> 00:05:35,440
It was fun to watch him and Dr. Yuh bickering. Too bad.

57
00:05:35,440 --> 00:05:37,570
Come on...

58
00:05:40,800 --> 00:05:43,680
It's kind of boring without him.

59
00:05:44,740 --> 00:05:47,160
But I'm sure he's doing well there.

60
00:05:57,150 --> 00:06:00,040
I'll have a soondae to go, ma'am.

61
00:06:05,560 --> 00:06:08,250
What are you thinking about so intently?

62
00:06:10,430 --> 00:06:12,580
When did you get here?

63
00:06:18,450 --> 00:06:21,370
Are things going well with So Jin?

64
00:06:23,820 --> 00:06:25,330
Yes.

65
00:06:28,360 --> 00:06:30,320
That's good to hear.

66
00:06:32,600 --> 00:06:35,110
Here you go.

67
00:06:35,110 --> 00:06:37,030
I gave you a lot of liver and lungs.

68
00:06:37,030 --> 00:06:38,900
Thank you.

69
00:06:39,490 --> 00:06:41,710
See you later, then.

70
00:06:43,030 --> 00:06:45,020
It's not going well.

71
00:06:46,510 --> 00:06:47,980
Pardon?

72
00:06:49,060 --> 00:06:51,210
I said it's not going well.

73
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:59,500
Should we grab a drink?

74
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:12,720
Eating like this isn't bad.

75
00:07:12,720 --> 00:07:14,840
It's kind of romantic, too.

76
00:07:14,840 --> 00:07:17,020
Did you say you come here often?

77
00:07:17,020 --> 00:07:21,260
Yes, it's a place with fond memories.

78
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:29,450
It's where So Jin and I first met as kids.

79
00:07:31,160 --> 00:07:35,750
Is it okay for me to be here, too?

80
00:07:39,290 --> 00:07:41,240
Yun Woo is gone now.

81
00:07:41,240 --> 00:07:44,750
You just need to make things work with So Jin now.

82
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:48,640
But you don't look so happy about it.

83
00:07:50,100 --> 00:07:51,860
I know.

84
00:07:52,400 --> 00:07:57,150
Feelings are so strange.

85
00:07:58,370 --> 00:08:03,680
I thought everything would be resolved without Hyung.

86
00:08:03,680 --> 00:08:05,950
But now that it happened,

87
00:08:07,350 --> 00:08:09,870
I no longer feel confident.

88
00:08:11,300 --> 00:08:17,920
I've asked myself for a long time if I could really

89
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:21,890
make her happy and satisfied.

90
00:08:22,750 --> 00:08:28,590
I've known the answer for a long time,

91
00:08:30,190 --> 00:08:33,000
but I think I've tried to deny it.

92
00:08:37,950 --> 00:08:41,260
How could you be exactly like me?

93
00:08:41,260 --> 00:08:43,470
I was like that, too.

94
00:08:43,470 --> 00:08:46,800
The other person didn't want it but just to feel better,

95
00:08:46,800 --> 00:08:49,880
I forced my feelings on him.

96
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:54,680
Thinking back, I was so selfish and bad.

97
00:08:54,680 --> 00:08:57,240
That's why I let him go.

98
00:08:58,050 --> 00:09:00,630
I don't know about anything else,

99
00:09:00,630 --> 00:09:02,760
but I think you're wrong about one thing.

100
00:09:02,760 --> 00:09:05,340
- Pardon? 
 - You aren't...

101
00:09:05,340 --> 00:09:08,600
a selfish and bad person, Mi Eun.

102
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:10,780
I can assure you that.

103
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:18,870
I didn't know you knew how to say stuff like that.

104
00:09:19,600 --> 00:09:22,540
They say people die if they suddenly change.

105
00:09:22,540 --> 00:09:24,620
Are you sure you aren't sick?

106
00:09:25,620 --> 00:09:28,090
- I'm not. 
 - You must be.

107
00:09:28,090 --> 00:09:30,080
How strange.

108
00:09:33,400 --> 00:09:37,470
What happened to my lungs and liver?

109
00:09:39,610 --> 00:09:41,070
So weird.

110
00:09:41,070 --> 00:09:46,900
I only ate a piece of liver and lungs. Where did it all go?

111
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:49,650
It wasn't me. I swear it wasn't me.

112
00:09:49,650 --> 00:09:52,080
Are you lying right now?

113
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:56,430
I-I only ate one. Hold on.

114
00:09:56,430 --> 00:09:57,720
Seriously.

115
00:09:57,720 --> 00:10:00,510
- Where did it go? 
 - Are you kidding me?

116
00:10:00,510 --> 00:10:03,110
It wasn't me. Did I eat it by mistake?

117
00:10:03,110 --> 00:10:05,810
I ate organs. I must've thought it was soondae.

118
00:10:05,810 --> 00:10:07,850
How strange. Why do you keep denying it?

119
00:10:07,850 --> 00:10:09,760
Where did it go?

120
00:10:09,760 --> 00:10:13,280
- Seriously. 
 - I see a piece, Mi Eun.

121
00:10:25,970 --> 00:10:28,240
Father.

122
00:10:29,040 --> 00:10:32,380
This is Anna.

123
00:10:36,320 --> 00:10:38,950
Where did he go?

124
00:10:38,950 --> 00:10:41,450
He has no mass, either.

125
00:11:37,780 --> 00:11:40,150
Father.

126
00:11:43,640 --> 00:11:47,150
Sister Anna, what brings you here?

127
00:11:56,950 --> 00:12:00,420
I was worried you didn't come to the mass.

128
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:04,340
Have you been here the entire time?

129
00:12:11,540 --> 00:12:13,680
Sister Anna.

130
00:12:15,290 --> 00:12:17,450
Yes, Father.

131
00:12:18,420 --> 00:12:21,040
I said I love God,

132
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:24,480
but I'm not able to love a person.

133
00:12:27,170 --> 00:12:30,580
God wants me to love people.

134
00:12:33,080 --> 00:12:35,680
I'm not qualified to be a priest.

135
00:12:37,710 --> 00:12:41,160
What do you mean by that?

136
00:12:41,160 --> 00:12:44,520
I knew Yi Myung was unhappy,

137
00:12:45,130 --> 00:12:48,640
but I never extended my hand once.

138
00:12:50,340 --> 00:12:52,200
Yi Myung...

139
00:12:53,800 --> 00:12:56,780
killed his former adoptive family, who abused him,

140
00:12:56,780 --> 00:12:59,860
and while he was in jail for it,

141
00:12:59,860 --> 00:13:03,120
he wrote me dozens of letters.

142
00:13:04,230 --> 00:13:06,200
But...

143
00:13:08,210 --> 00:13:11,330
I never responded once.

144
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,610
I just asked God to...

145
00:13:17,110 --> 00:13:21,730
be responsible for Yi Myung instead.

146
00:13:22,900 --> 00:13:25,000
I turned my back on him.

147
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,890
 Yi Myung. Yi Myung! 

148
00:13:27,890 --> 00:13:29,720
 Yi Myung! 

149
00:13:29,720 --> 00:13:32,080
 Yi Myung! 

150
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:36,540
 He stole my priest uniform and Bible and kept them, 

151
00:13:36,540 --> 00:13:39,520
 perhaps because he missed me. 

152
00:13:40,710 --> 00:13:45,130
 But I never gave him attention once. 

153
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:48,370
 If I saw him... 

154
00:13:49,640 --> 00:13:54,030
I thought I'd be consumed by his darkness.

155
00:13:54,030 --> 00:13:56,570
- I was afraid of that— 
 - No.

156
00:13:57,980 --> 00:14:03,240
You love people, Father.

157
00:14:04,000 --> 00:14:08,940
 You came inside the abandoned armoire to save me because 

158
00:14:08,940 --> 00:14:12,250
you cared about me as a person, didn't you?

159
00:14:12,250 --> 00:14:13,920
I was...

160
00:14:15,700 --> 00:14:20,490
comforted by you then, Sister Anna.

161
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:30,290
As long as I'm a priest,

162
00:14:32,410 --> 00:14:36,430
I won't be able to love anyone.

163
00:15:26,140 --> 00:15:29,050
All done. Let's go.

164
00:15:36,070 --> 00:15:39,710
You can't be obsessed with a winter scarf in summer.

165
00:15:39,710 --> 00:15:44,990
You don't believe what I said about the yarn of fate, do you?

166
00:15:46,490 --> 00:15:49,570
I just want to gift it to her.

167
00:15:49,570 --> 00:15:52,680
- You know how she gets cold easily. 
 - Who?

168
00:15:53,270 --> 00:15:55,090
So Jin.

169
00:15:55,840 --> 00:15:58,520
- Kang Hoon, do you— 
 - It's not like that.

170
00:15:58,520 --> 00:16:03,690
I want her to wear this scarf and meet someone nice.

171
00:16:05,350 --> 00:16:12,470
She needs to find someone she can never forget, like you did.

172
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:14,800
How about you?

173
00:16:28,250 --> 00:16:30,960
- Hello. 
 - Ms. Oh, Ms. Oh, you won't believe this.

174
00:16:30,960 --> 00:16:32,540
Do you know what I saw?

175
00:16:32,540 --> 00:16:34,360
Watch this.

176
00:16:36,210 --> 00:16:38,650
 - Hello.  
 - Ta-da!

177
00:16:38,650 --> 00:16:41,620
- Gosh. 
 - Doesn't he look amazing on TV?

178
00:16:41,620 --> 00:16:44,340
He's a celebrity. I'll ask for his autograph later.

179
00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:45,880
Don't be too excited.

180
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,170
- He's introducing himself. 
 - Here we go.

181
00:16:47,170 --> 00:16:51,700
 I'm Gwang Su from 23rd Street of Singlesville. 

182
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:56,770
 I'm 36 years old. I was born in '88. 

183
00:16:56,770 --> 00:16:59,810
 I live in Gangnam-gu, Seoul. 

184
00:16:59,810 --> 00:17:05,130
 I'm an endourologist at Shim Hospital in Cheongdam-dong. 

185
00:17:06,220 --> 00:17:10,720
 I have a job, a car, 

186
00:17:10,720 --> 00:17:12,380
 and I have many friends, too. 

187
00:17:12,380 --> 00:17:15,500
 But there's one thing I don't have. 

188
00:17:15,500 --> 00:17:17,470
 That's... 

189
00:17:21,440 --> 00:17:23,260
 To be honest... 

190
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:26,720
 I'm sterile. 

191
00:17:26,720 --> 00:17:31,980
 But instead of devoting my money and time to children, 

192
00:17:31,980 --> 00:17:36,100
 I'll fully focus on my wife and myself. 

193
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:41,440
I'd love to meet a woman who wants to be a DINK couple with me.

194
00:17:41,440 --> 00:17:43,160
Thank you.

195
00:17:47,190 --> 00:17:50,170
What's your ideal type?

196
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:56,670
I like someone who's petite, delicate, and feminine.

197
00:17:59,560 --> 00:18:01,560
I used to, but...

198
00:18:01,560 --> 00:18:07,670
I recently had a relationship that changed my entire life.

199
00:18:07,670 --> 00:18:09,100
It changed me a lot.

200
00:18:09,100 --> 00:18:11,200
 I don't have an ideal type currently. 

201
00:18:11,200 --> 00:18:17,320
Any of you here can become my ideal type.

202
00:18:19,050 --> 00:18:20,640
 What's your hobby? 

203
00:18:20,640 --> 00:18:22,130
 Do you like to exercise? 

204
00:18:22,130 --> 00:18:23,690
 I never did before, 

205
00:18:23,690 --> 00:18:25,790
 but I really enjoy it now. 

206
00:18:25,790 --> 00:18:30,400
 I tend to care for myself strictly. 

207
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:35,720
I want to go to a foot bath spa when I get a girlfriend and...

208
00:18:37,760 --> 00:18:39,250
 I'm embarrassed of my feet. 

209
00:18:39,250 --> 00:18:40,760
 Why? 

210
00:18:40,760 --> 00:18:43,660
 They're the prettiest feet in the world. 

211
00:18:49,700 --> 00:18:53,120
I want to watch a movie at a drive-in theater once a week, too.

212
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:55,480
 Call me Jung Tam. 

213
00:18:55,480 --> 00:18:57,830
 Don't call me Dr. Yuh. 

214
00:18:57,830 --> 00:19:01,140
 Or call me, "My dear cutie." 

215
00:19:01,140 --> 00:19:03,270
 Even after getting married, 

216
00:19:03,270 --> 00:19:08,680
I'd like to think of each day as a lovey-dovey date.

217
00:19:10,500 --> 00:19:13,840
 I'm actually planning to become a DINK, too. 

218
00:19:13,840 --> 00:19:15,790
 I see. 

219
00:19:18,670 --> 00:19:21,190
It hasn't been that long since we broke up!

220
00:19:23,220 --> 00:19:24,350
Celebrity. Celebrity. Celebrity.

221
00:19:24,350 --> 00:19:26,240
Stand back. Stand back.

222
00:19:26,240 --> 00:19:28,470
Hello.

223
00:19:28,470 --> 00:19:31,300
Dr. Yuh, why do you look so good on TV?

224
00:19:31,300 --> 00:19:33,320
Will you become popular now?

225
00:19:33,320 --> 00:19:35,390
An autograph, please.

226
00:19:35,390 --> 00:19:37,450
I'm not popular.

227
00:19:37,450 --> 00:19:38,950
Why do you look so sad?

228
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,660
Because I'm lonely.

229
00:19:40,660 --> 00:19:42,850
Didn't you find a match?

230
00:19:42,850 --> 00:19:44,830
What is it? I want a spoiler.

231
00:19:44,830 --> 00:19:47,110
Aren't you going to Thailand?

232
00:19:47,110 --> 00:19:49,270
I don't know.

233
00:19:49,270 --> 00:19:51,450
He shouldn't have mentioned he was sterile.

234
00:19:51,450 --> 00:19:53,350
I know. He drives me crazy.

235
00:19:53,350 --> 00:19:55,150
Here's your order.

236
00:19:55,150 --> 00:19:57,250
Thank you.

237
