238
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:13,700
   

239
00:20:15,040 --> 00:20:18,730
Is the project preparation going well?

240
00:20:18,730 --> 00:20:22,690
I'm sorry. I know you're having a hard time already.

241
00:20:22,690 --> 00:20:25,910
It's okay. I need to keep work and life separate.

242
00:20:25,910 --> 00:20:29,880
But I'm worried about the theme.

243
00:20:29,880 --> 00:20:32,440
How about you try to make it work?

244
00:20:32,440 --> 00:20:34,020
A romantic project.

245
00:20:34,020 --> 00:20:37,890
You might as well do it officially.

246
00:20:39,660 --> 00:20:41,610
I'm not so sure.

247
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:46,370
Excuse me.

248
00:20:46,370 --> 00:20:49,140
   

249
00:20:49,140 --> 00:20:50,420
Hello?

250
00:20:50,420 --> 00:20:52,350
Hey, what's going on?

251
00:20:56,060 --> 00:20:57,590
What?

252
00:20:59,110 --> 00:21:01,140
Okay.

253
00:21:01,140 --> 00:21:04,060
I'll head over right now. Okay.

254
00:21:11,100 --> 00:21:13,980
Team Leader Han, is something wrong?

255
00:21:13,980 --> 00:21:18,500
- What's wrong? 
 - Oh, I— I—

256
00:21:18,500 --> 00:21:21,900
BK... I'll go home early today.

257
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:23,350
I'll tell you the details tomorrow.

258
00:21:23,350 --> 00:21:24,790
I'm sorry. I'll go.

259
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:26,440
Okay.

260
00:21:35,170 --> 00:21:36,850
Mom.

261
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:40,100
Hey.

262
00:21:42,020 --> 00:21:44,400
Why didn't you tell me?

263
00:21:45,860 --> 00:21:47,410
What's the big deal?

264
00:21:47,410 --> 00:21:49,490
You don't have to worry.

265
00:21:50,960 --> 00:21:52,790
It is a big deal.

266
00:21:52,790 --> 00:21:56,000
You should've told me, at least.

267
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:59,600
- Who else would you talk to but me? 
 - Mi Eun,

268
00:22:00,790 --> 00:22:04,430
death isn't tragic. It's natural.

269
00:22:04,970 --> 00:22:11,540
I'm still so happy I'm an artist who's inspired by death.

270
00:22:11,540 --> 00:22:13,110
At least, you need to understand me, okay?

271
00:22:13,110 --> 00:22:14,320
Mom.

272
00:22:14,320 --> 00:22:16,500
What do you mean, understand?

273
00:22:16,500 --> 00:22:19,070
Do I have to hear about you dying from the news?

274
00:22:19,070 --> 00:22:21,850
Mi Eun, I think you should leave now.

275
00:22:21,850 --> 00:22:24,590
Okay, Mom. I'll come back.

276
00:22:29,750 --> 00:22:31,270
And what's with this show?

277
00:22:31,270 --> 00:22:35,180
You barely have time for surgery and go through chemo.

278
00:22:35,180 --> 00:22:38,180
What's this stupid show for, anyway?

279
00:22:38,180 --> 00:22:40,480
You want me to cut out my lungs,

280
00:22:41,110 --> 00:22:44,810
take anticancer drugs, throw up, and pass out.

281
00:22:44,810 --> 00:22:47,570
See how much it spread in my organs,

282
00:22:47,570 --> 00:22:51,390
including bones, eyes, and brain, to what extent,

283
00:22:51,390 --> 00:22:53,930
and die while trembling in fear?

284
00:22:53,930 --> 00:22:56,250
Why do you think about dying first?

285
00:22:56,250 --> 00:22:59,310
Many get surgery, become cancer-free, and live healthy.

286
00:22:59,310 --> 00:23:03,420
I'll get surgery once the show ends.

287
00:23:03,420 --> 00:23:05,790
What if the cancer spreads in the meantime?

288
00:23:05,790 --> 00:23:07,240
It's my disease!

289
00:23:07,240 --> 00:23:09,620
It has nothing to do with you.

290
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:11,100
What?

291
00:23:13,260 --> 00:23:15,600
If you feel that bad,

292
00:23:15,600 --> 00:23:18,780
have a show in memory of me after I die.

293
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:22,110
Mom, you really are...

294
00:23:22,990 --> 00:23:25,680
selfish until the end.

295
00:23:26,630 --> 00:23:29,220
Don't you care about So Ri and me?

296
00:23:35,210 --> 00:23:39,910
I can't burden you now after doing nothing for you.

297
00:23:39,910 --> 00:23:44,280
I've been living fighting my fate and nothing else.

298
00:23:44,280 --> 00:23:49,470
My fate ended up bringing me here,

299
00:23:49,470 --> 00:23:53,050
but you don't have to get sucked into it.

300
00:23:53,860 --> 00:23:59,850
I won't apologize to you or anyone else.

301
00:23:59,850 --> 00:24:07,150
So, don't demand to have a mom all of a sudden

302
00:24:07,150 --> 00:24:10,410
and live well individually.

303
00:24:10,410 --> 00:24:12,870
As you always have.

304
00:24:30,930 --> 00:24:32,990
 Catch me. Catch me. 

305
00:24:32,990 --> 00:24:35,130
 Catch me! 

306
00:24:35,130 --> 00:24:38,130
 Be careful. Catch me! Catch me! 

307
00:24:38,130 --> 00:24:40,800
 - Be careful. Be careful. 
 - I'm going to get you. 

308
00:24:43,810 --> 00:24:45,810
 I'll catch you! 

309
00:24:45,810 --> 00:24:47,900
 I'll catch you! 

310
00:24:48,690 --> 00:24:51,420
 I'm getting close! 

311
00:25:09,970 --> 00:25:12,330
Things went the way you wanted.

312
00:25:13,300 --> 00:25:17,480
So Ri and I aren't weak.

313
00:25:23,140 --> 00:25:26,280
Even if you disappeared from this world,

314
00:25:28,370 --> 00:25:30,950
we'll never crumble.

315
00:25:33,600 --> 00:25:35,560
So,

316
00:25:37,620 --> 00:25:39,790
you should live, too.

317
00:25:47,660 --> 00:25:51,400
Keep fighting the way you have, or do whatever you want.

318
00:25:52,850 --> 00:25:58,200
Don't let us see you succumb to your fate.

319
00:26:11,100 --> 00:26:13,030
Mom...

320
00:26:19,110 --> 00:26:21,890
What is this, a tragic drama?

321
00:26:25,910 --> 00:26:28,790
This is so annoying...

322
00:26:49,130 --> 00:26:52,840
When you introduced yourself, you mentioned meeting true love.

323
00:26:52,840 --> 00:26:56,520
- Yes. 
 - Why did you end up breaking up?

324
00:26:58,530 --> 00:27:00,860
Well...

325
00:27:00,860 --> 00:27:05,310
I was confident I could only love her for the rest of my life,

326
00:27:05,310 --> 00:27:09,980
but I guess that wasn't quite enough for her.

327
00:27:14,010 --> 00:27:15,750
To be honest,

328
00:27:16,990 --> 00:27:20,040
just looking at this makes me miss her a lot.

329
00:27:22,770 --> 00:27:26,060
I miss her so much that— I'm going crazy.

330
00:27:26,060 --> 00:27:28,390
   
   

331
00:27:28,390 --> 00:27:29,570
   
   

332
00:27:29,570 --> 00:27:31,590
Look at him crying. Isn't he so funny?

333
00:27:31,590 --> 00:27:34,600
Why does he cry so pitifully?

334
00:27:37,330 --> 00:27:39,740
- Seriously. 
 - My gosh.

335
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:41,880
Do you find that funny?

336
00:27:42,510 --> 00:27:44,790
Do you find that funny?

337
00:27:44,790 --> 00:27:48,000
Geez, what's her deal?

338
00:27:48,840 --> 00:27:51,700
Why did I come all the way here?

339
00:27:55,200 --> 00:27:58,420
Why did he have to cry on TV?

340
00:28:12,200 --> 00:28:14,200
Oh, no...

341
00:28:19,840 --> 00:28:21,370
Take care.

342
00:28:21,370 --> 00:28:22,580
Hold on. Let's talk—

343
00:28:22,580 --> 00:28:24,350
- Let go. 
 - Let's talk.

344
00:28:24,350 --> 00:28:27,390
Do we have more to talk about?

345
00:28:28,900 --> 00:28:33,000
You must have good news to tell after meeting a fellow DINK.

346
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:36,130
Did you watch "I'm Single"?

347
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:44,060
No, I don't watch stuff like that because I'm busy.

348
00:28:44,060 --> 00:28:45,690
Take care.

349
00:28:45,690 --> 00:28:47,110
Hold on, hold on!

350
00:28:47,110 --> 00:28:49,130
I didn't go on the show because I wanted to.

351
00:28:49,130 --> 00:28:51,640
A friend of mine is the show's producer.

352
00:28:51,640 --> 00:28:54,130
One of the contestants suddenly canceled on them.

353
00:28:54,130 --> 00:28:56,570
So, he begged me to fill in. I did it against my will.

354
00:28:56,570 --> 00:28:58,370
You don't have to explain to me.

355
00:28:58,370 --> 00:29:02,060
It's because I don't want you to misunderstand me.

356
00:29:03,690 --> 00:29:07,300
I thought about you the entire time I was there.

357
00:29:07,300 --> 00:29:10,560
I wasn't interested in any of the women there.

358
00:29:15,090 --> 00:29:18,180
Did you really not miss me at all?

359
00:29:21,550 --> 00:29:25,850
I missed you a lot, Sung Mi.

360
00:29:29,650 --> 00:29:32,170
I didn't miss you.

361
00:29:37,410 --> 00:29:41,090
Can't you look me in the eyes and say it?

362
00:29:43,040 --> 00:29:47,060
I didn't miss you.

363
00:29:53,060 --> 00:29:54,740
Sung Mi,

364
00:29:56,100 --> 00:29:58,030
I love you.

365
00:30:07,010 --> 00:30:09,550
Why are you doing this?

366
00:30:09,550 --> 00:30:11,640
What do you mean?

367
00:30:12,790 --> 00:30:15,580
Let go of me.

368
00:30:15,580 --> 00:30:17,350
Stay still.

369
00:30:17,350 --> 00:30:18,910
Okay.

370
00:30:29,490 --> 00:30:31,990
   

371
00:31:06,680 --> 00:31:09,410
I don't think I gave up on my faith.

372
00:31:09,410 --> 00:31:14,100
I finally destroyed my greenhouse and got free.

373
00:31:16,020 --> 00:31:18,550
I know, Father.

374
00:31:18,550 --> 00:31:23,270
This is also your path to God, right?

375
00:31:27,500 --> 00:31:31,350
   

376
00:31:43,850 --> 00:31:45,320
Kang Hoon.

377
00:31:45,320 --> 00:31:46,920
Noona.

378
00:31:49,270 --> 00:31:53,680
The night air is nice. Do you want to go somewhere with me?

379
00:31:53,680 --> 00:31:55,420
You know, right?

380
00:31:56,420 --> 00:31:59,460
Whenever my relationships failed,

381
00:31:59,460 --> 00:32:06,680
I came here to curse and hate the jerks who hurt me.

382
00:32:06,680 --> 00:32:08,860
But this time,

383
00:32:10,150 --> 00:32:14,880
I keep hating myself instead.

384
00:32:18,150 --> 00:32:20,500
I thought Yun Woo...

385
00:32:21,620 --> 00:32:24,740
abandoned me and ran away.

386
00:32:24,740 --> 00:32:26,300
But...

387
00:32:27,690 --> 00:32:31,650
I was the one who ran away.

388
00:32:34,590 --> 00:32:38,030
Because our DNA wasn't compatible,

389
00:32:38,030 --> 00:32:41,850
I ignored my feelings toward him.

390
00:32:42,810 --> 00:32:46,260
In case I'd get hurt if we weren't meant to be,

391
00:32:47,810 --> 00:32:53,360
I refused to believe Yun Woo's true feelings.

392
00:33:00,080 --> 00:33:02,270
That's why I want to...

393
00:33:04,190 --> 00:33:06,830
finally become brave.

394
00:33:08,750 --> 00:33:12,950
Instead of relying on DNA or fate,

395
00:33:14,300 --> 00:33:16,950
I'll try following...

396
00:33:18,130 --> 00:33:20,180
my heart.

397
00:33:21,500 --> 00:33:26,790
What if Yun Woo never comes back? I mean...

398
00:33:28,200 --> 00:33:33,230
what if he came back but didn't love you anymore?

399
00:33:35,830 --> 00:33:37,750
I'll cry.

400
00:33:38,550 --> 00:33:42,370
I'll cry, struggle,

401
00:33:42,370 --> 00:33:44,640
and overcome it.

402
00:34:15,280 --> 00:34:17,170
Can I...

403
00:34:18,370 --> 00:34:20,360
hug you just once?

404
00:34:38,590 --> 00:34:42,180
♫  Every empty spot  ♫

405
00:34:42,180 --> 00:34:45,870
♫  Of my heart  ♫

406
00:34:45,870 --> 00:34:48,540
♫  Is colored by you  ♫

407
00:34:48,540 --> 00:34:52,750
♫  Who came to me without words  ♫

408
00:34:52,750 --> 00:34:57,220
I'm free! I'm finally free from Han So Jin!

409
00:35:00,140 --> 00:35:02,040
You go ahead.

410
00:35:02,570 --> 00:35:04,740
Hurry up.

411
00:35:07,760 --> 00:35:13,130
♫  As the days we spend together  ♫

412
00:35:13,130 --> 00:35:15,330
- Bye. 
 - I'll leave, then.

413
00:35:15,330 --> 00:35:21,530
♫  I find myself thinking of you endlessly  ♫

414
00:35:22,400 --> 00:35:26,720
♫  The story we will paint together  ♫

415
00:35:26,720 --> 00:35:30,090
♫  Feels so vivid to me ♫

416
00:35:30,090 --> 00:35:34,060
♫  I wish that this moment, looking at you  ♫

417
00:35:34,060 --> 00:35:38,130
♫  Could last forever ♫

418
00:35:52,720 --> 00:35:55,910
I chose the perfect time to come.

419
00:35:56,730 --> 00:35:59,220
What brings you here?

420
00:36:01,630 --> 00:36:03,100
Well...

421
00:36:04,100 --> 00:36:06,620
I couldn't sleep and...

422
00:36:06,620 --> 00:36:08,930
I felt lonelier than usual today.

423
00:36:08,930 --> 00:36:11,730
But for some reason, I thought of this place.

424
00:36:13,110 --> 00:36:17,360
I thought I might as well check if you were here, too.

425
00:36:17,360 --> 00:36:19,460
But you were actually here.

426
00:36:19,460 --> 00:36:22,180
Looks like we actually have a lot in common.

427
00:36:29,370 --> 00:36:31,700
Have you seen the movie, "Notebook"?

428
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:39,320
"My name will soon be forgotten,

429
00:36:39,320 --> 00:36:42,600
but I've loved another with all my heart and soul,

430
00:36:42,600 --> 00:36:45,120
and to me, this has always been enough."

431
00:36:47,590 --> 00:36:50,230
You're just like that.

432
00:36:51,480 --> 00:36:54,390
So Jin is so foolish.

433
00:36:54,390 --> 00:36:56,530
How could she reject someone like you?

434
00:37:01,920 --> 00:37:05,950
I suppose you're right.

435
00:37:07,220 --> 00:37:10,370
A part of me is still sore,

436
00:37:10,370 --> 00:37:13,040
but I feel better.

437
00:37:13,040 --> 00:37:16,440
See? I was right, wasn't I?

438
00:37:16,440 --> 00:37:19,740
I hope Noona becomes happy.

439
00:37:19,740 --> 00:37:21,800
She will be.

440
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:25,310
She's stronger than you think.

441
00:37:26,930 --> 00:37:31,340
Since we were both rejected,

442
00:37:31,340 --> 00:37:33,720
should we drink together?

443
00:37:33,720 --> 00:37:35,660
We can't drink here.

444
00:37:36,840 --> 00:37:39,010
- I'm sorry. Are you okay? 
 - I'm sorry.

445
00:37:39,010 --> 00:37:40,580
Here.

446
00:37:41,580 --> 00:37:43,240
Thank you.

447
00:37:48,480 --> 00:37:53,500
You seem way more thoughtful than I thought.

448
00:37:53,500 --> 00:37:55,730
You carry stuff like this, too.

449
00:37:56,530 --> 00:38:02,480
Since So Jin is so clumsy and messy,

450
00:38:02,480 --> 00:38:05,650
I started carrying it around at some point.

451
00:38:06,820 --> 00:38:09,170
But I won't need it anymore.

452
00:38:10,220 --> 00:38:11,820
You never know.

453
00:38:11,820 --> 00:38:16,200
A woman you want to care for might show up again.

454
00:38:25,200 --> 00:38:27,980
Should we get going now?

455
00:38:33,210 --> 00:38:36,240
Do you want to catch a midnight screening?

456
00:38:36,240 --> 00:38:39,230
Let's try changing your mood completely.

457
00:38:39,230 --> 00:38:41,070
At this hour?

458
00:38:41,940 --> 00:38:44,880
You can refresh your mood anytime and anywhere.

459
00:38:45,900 --> 00:38:47,500
Let's get going.

460
00:38:49,310 --> 00:38:50,550
Don't mind me.

461
00:38:50,550 --> 00:38:53,720
Seriously. I said you can't drink here.

462
00:38:54,670 --> 00:38:57,180
   

463
00:38:59,100 --> 00:39:01,280
   

464
00:39:06,820 --> 00:39:10,630
   

465
00:39:12,070 --> 00:39:18,240
 These days, I'm finding answers for the hardships I've faced. 

466
00:39:18,240 --> 00:39:21,460
   

467
00:39:21,900 --> 00:39:24,690
   

468
00:39:24,960 --> 00:39:30,140
 There's one question I haven't found the answer to yet. 

469
00:39:43,200 --> 00:39:47,370
   

470
00:40:32,260 --> 00:40:34,760
 Ta-da! Yun Woo, 

471
00:40:34,760 --> 00:40:38,810
 I made your favorite, gopchang tteokbokki. Have a look. 

472
00:40:38,810 --> 00:40:41,610
 Here. What do you think? 

473
00:40:41,610 --> 00:40:45,230
Mom, gopchang tteokbokki has to be spicy.

474
00:40:45,230 --> 00:40:47,540
 What? Really? 

475
00:40:47,540 --> 00:40:50,410
 That's why it wasn't good. 

476
00:40:50,410 --> 00:40:53,190
 But you can't eat spicy food. 

477
00:40:53,190 --> 00:41:00,050
 I'll make you royal tteobkokki with beef and soy sauce when I visit Korea. 

478
00:41:00,050 --> 00:41:01,390
Are you visiting Korea?

479
00:41:01,390 --> 00:41:03,410
 Of course, I have to. 

480
00:41:03,410 --> 00:41:05,930
 You said you were opening a hospital in the countryside. 

481
00:41:05,930 --> 00:41:09,210
 You must be tired. I should take care of you. 

482
00:41:09,210 --> 00:41:10,660
I'm not opening a hospital.

483
00:41:10,660 --> 00:41:13,520
I got hired as a general practitioner.

484
00:41:13,520 --> 00:41:14,850
 What? 

485
00:41:15,760 --> 00:41:17,430
 You got hired? 

486
00:41:17,430 --> 00:41:20,220
 Why? Is it because of your hand? 

487
00:41:20,220 --> 00:41:21,730
No.

488
00:41:21,730 --> 00:41:25,770
I need some time to get used to living here.

489
00:41:26,590 --> 00:41:28,450
See you soon, Mom.

490
00:41:34,670 --> 00:41:37,020
Is it curry today?

491
00:41:37,020 --> 00:41:39,030
The kids would be happy.

492
00:41:40,970 --> 00:41:42,550
Hello.

493
00:41:44,930 --> 00:41:47,120
Thank you.

494
00:41:47,120 --> 00:41:49,600
It's been only a month, but you look better.

495
00:41:49,600 --> 00:41:51,220
Do I?

496
00:41:53,550 --> 00:41:57,970
Being around children makes me happy and gives me so much energy!

497
00:41:57,970 --> 00:42:03,790
I feel closer to God, whom I've been searching for, too.

498
00:42:03,790 --> 00:42:06,170
I can definitely tell.

499
00:42:06,170 --> 00:42:10,050
This suits you more than the priest's uniform.

500
00:42:10,050 --> 00:42:13,130
I'm envious that you look happier, too.

501
00:42:13,130 --> 00:42:16,320
You're right. I'm happy.

502
00:42:16,320 --> 00:42:18,980
Thank you for doing volunteer work so often.

503
00:42:18,980 --> 00:42:20,720
It's not work.

504
00:42:20,720 --> 00:42:24,140
I come here once a month to be healed, too.

505
00:42:24,140 --> 00:42:28,490
Everyone wants to be happy, after all.

506
00:42:28,490 --> 00:42:32,480
Me, the children here,

507
00:42:32,480 --> 00:42:36,860
you, and Yi Myung, too.

508
00:42:38,380 --> 00:42:41,000
No, we need to go inside now.

509
00:42:41,000 --> 00:42:42,410
Let's go.

510
00:42:42,410 --> 00:42:44,720
Oh, come on.

511
00:42:46,350 --> 00:42:47,900
So Jin!

512
00:42:47,900 --> 00:42:50,310
Wha— What took you so long?

513
00:42:50,310 --> 00:42:53,010
Guys, it's Aunt So Jin.

514
00:42:53,010 --> 00:42:55,450
Say hello to her.

515
00:42:55,450 --> 00:42:57,970
Let's go!

516
00:42:59,620 --> 00:43:01,880
Long time no see. Have you been well?

517
00:43:01,880 --> 00:43:04,070
Hold on, hold on. I can't drop this.

518
00:43:04,070 --> 00:43:06,410
- Let me carry that. 
 - Thank you.

519
00:43:06,410 --> 00:43:08,620
- Take your time. 
 - Okay.

520
00:43:11,030 --> 00:43:12,620
Ah Ri.

521
00:43:14,330 --> 00:43:16,670
She's changed. She's changed.

522
00:43:17,500 --> 00:43:20,300
Should we start with Min Jae?

523
00:43:20,300 --> 00:43:24,100
Min Jae, I told you to eat a lot of veggies last time.

524
00:43:24,100 --> 00:43:26,770
- Did you do that for a month? 
 - No.

525
00:43:26,770 --> 00:43:28,830
Why not? You promised me.

526
00:43:28,830 --> 00:43:34,350
But there's so much tasty food besides veggies.

527
00:43:34,350 --> 00:43:36,210
I like meat.

528
00:43:36,210 --> 00:43:40,140
But still. You promised me. Try to do it this time, okay?

529
00:43:40,140 --> 00:43:41,650
Promise.

530
00:43:41,650 --> 00:43:44,650
Ms. Han, I kept my promise.

531
00:43:44,650 --> 00:43:46,980
I jump roped 100 times every day.

532
00:43:46,980 --> 00:43:49,030
I'll grow a lot taller, right?

533
00:43:49,030 --> 00:43:51,320
Wow, Yoon Soo.

534
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,660
Let's high-five first.

535
00:43:53,660 --> 00:43:55,810
Good job. But you have to keep at it.

536
00:43:55,810 --> 00:43:58,110
- Okay. 
 - Promise.

537
00:43:58,110 --> 00:44:00,600
- Okay, next. 
 - Let's break up.

538
00:44:01,430 --> 00:44:02,970
What?

539
00:44:02,970 --> 00:44:04,560
You said we were meant to be.

540
00:44:04,560 --> 00:44:06,520
How could love change?

541
00:44:06,520 --> 00:44:07,930
Why are you acting like a child?

542
00:44:07,930 --> 00:44:10,240
We both like black beans...

543
00:44:10,240 --> 00:44:12,490
